nuscript followed by a new edition of 53 anonymous poems. Each poem is presented as a diplomatic transcription with critical editorial commentary. A synoptic index allows the reader to place the manuscript within the wider context of the written tradition of older northern French poetry.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFrench poetryyTo 1500xManuscripts. 0aSongs, French. 4aAltfranzösisch. 4aChansonnier français. 4aEdition. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / French.2bisacsh  aChansonnier Français.  aEdition.  aOld French.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012z97831103011680 cprintz978311026344240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311026345940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110263459423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110263459/original  a978-3-11-030116-8  E-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012c2010d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2011  aZDB-23-DGGb2011  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014